Joliene wakes up in a weird sci-fi pod that has opened outward. The rest of the room looks like a pretty plain bedroom, with a dresser and desk.

She is in the body she inhabits on earth.
Her PDA has a new message visible. #soul-joliene
SOUL: Hey. Joliene, right? Sorry for pulling you into this mess, but something's gone wrong and this was the one idea I had.
Where on Earth have I returned to? What is the meaning of this?
SOUL: You’re in DC. Not very far from where you’ve already been when on Earth. Kind of fortunate compared to the absurd jumping around your fellow Arcticans have done.
I suppose that isn't the worst location for me to work with. Define "this mess". Why am I here?

SOUL: There's a man named John Leiblich trying to screw with the project in a very particular way. One of them involves indefinitely detaining Bruce Praxis, which he is doing in a complex directly connected to the one you've awoken in. At the very least, I'm aware you have an interest of some kind in the man.
((John Leiblich))

It's not personal, but yes, I would strongly prefer to get this man back in Arctica in one piece. Can you not bring him back home with him imprisoned? I'm still not clear on how these body transfers work, and you clearly have access to their use, so I should ask.

SOUL: No, it can't be done arbitrarily. I personally have much more limited access to things than PH, and even he has to go through a lot of hassle when he agrees to bring people over that aren't participants.
I see. Who's at the top of this food chain? Is it Virtos?
SOUL: TGP? I dunno, I always got the sense they were equal partners. Or at least trying to be. He's probably way more in control than PH right now, given PH's life is falling apart.
Then I'm sorry to hear about that. What do you propose I do about the Leiblich situation?

SOUL: I don't know. I have no idea what things are like on your side. But once you reach him, try to negotiate with or trick him. My understanding is he's an absurdly quixotic man that will abandon a pursuit as soon as he deems it unnecessary.
Joliene visibly panics after reading the words "negotiate or trick".

The door to the room Joliene is in slams open, revealing the queen herself.

Zita Praxis stares in confusion at Joliene, panting heavily. "Where is this!? What the hell have you done?"
And as soon as Zita comes through the door, she recomposes herself. This makes sense, yes. "...We are in a place called Washington DC. I did not do anything. We're going to see your son, Bruce."
She switches from panic to rage. "Don't you *dare* fuck with me! I don't know what two-bit intel you think you're running off of, but you can't threaten me with a life already lost!"
"Threaten you-" She visibly recoils in shock. "Your Highness, p- please, calm down. Why would I ever threaten you? I promise you, I-... do you recognize me?"

"No! I--I'm..." She breathes deeply. "I-- may have made an incorrect conclusion. This room here is... similar to the one I found myself in. Perhaps you are also a victim. But I don't know who you are. ...I suppose that's no reason to be certain of the worst on its own." 
She stares back out into the hall outside this room. "I am Zita Praxis. Though you seem to know that already. Where did you hear the name 'Bruce' from?"

"...Erm." She pauses for a while, a finger tapping at her chin, trying desperately to think of the most delicate way to phrase her reply. "...Zita. This is Joliene. I was... I was afraid of something like this happen-... urgh. This is going to take far too long to explain. Would you please come with me?"
"Joliene?" She narrows her eyes. "Your speech mannerisms are similar... and that would be a bizarre lie to choose. I still feel this whole situation is suspect... but I'll extend some faith to you."
"You're right. It is suspect. Just, ah..." She pauses once again, shorter this time. "I don't know. Just- just follow me." She exits the room and assesses her surroundings.
There's four doors on the wall Joliene just emerged from, two of which are already open (you opened one), and one on the opposite side of the wall. Nothing else notable is here.
She opens the door on the opposite side and looks through.

Opening the door seems to trigger some kind of automatic function. The lights come on to illuminate this twelve sided room, and a hologram of a man Joliene does not recognize materializes.

“Welcome to the standard cognitive aptitude assessment. I’m Sheeval Deltent, and I’ll act as your guide. The goal of this exercise is to ensure no cognitive or physical deterioration has occurred through the process of virtual travel. The four doors to your left and right lead to short puzzle-esque challenges relating to basic comprehension of the world around you. The door directly opposite the one you entered from will open once all the others have been completed, after which you will meet with an associate of UNICR for a short interview. For assistance, or if you urgently need to exit from these premises, stand on the central tile.” He points below the feet of the hologram. “This message is pre-recorded, but you can contact me at sdelt@mit.edu for complaints. Please progress at your own pace.” He vanishes.

Zita stares at this man for the entire period of time he appears, completely bewildered. She then turns to Joliene. “What?”
This paragraph rules
"Ah- this is normal. Not anticipated, but... normal. Right. Um, please come with me." She enters the door closest to her left while tapping at her PDA.
Who the fuck is Sheeval Deltent?
SOUL: Some guy. He would’ve had some control over the area you’re in, but I never really kept up with his personal projects.
SOUL: He’s dead now, at any rate. But he probably would’ve had some role in your whole experience with this project if he wasn’t.
He's dead? His hologram is currently trying to test my cognitive abilities. Why should I follow the instructions of a dead man? I must get to Bruce.
SOUL: Oh, christ. Him and PH and their stupid fuckin’ puzzle rooms.
SOUL: You should just be able to skip the whole thing? I doubt he’d actually implement something that automatically locked it while the whole thing was unmanned.

There is a plaque on the wall of this room that reads the following:

> You are driving a bus, a form of automated vehicle. At the 1st stop of the day, 8 people get on board. At the 2nd stop, 4 people get off and 11 people get on. At the 3rd stop, 2 people get off and 6 people get on. At the 4th stop, 13 people get off and 1 person gets on. At the 5th stop 5 people get off and 3 people get on. At the 6th stop 3 people get off and 2 people get on. What color are the bus driver’s eyes?

Beneath this is a keyboard.
She types "a dark grey or something".
Hologram Sheeval arrives again. “That’s probably right. Spotting the trick is what matters. 2/4 doors completed.”
She quirks a brow, then checks inside each of the other three rooms in succession.
Zita’s in one of the four, muttering to herself.
"Did you solve the riddle here, Zita?"

“I did one of the other rooms. It was some nonsense about color theory. This one, ah…”
She’s visibly uncomfortable, and walks away from the input device. “I’ll… do the other one that’s left. More efficient for us to split the work up.”
"...hm. May I ask what the precise question was? Don't tell me the answer."
“You… can look for yourself. I’ll be done in just a second.” She leaves for one of the other doors.
"Hmn. Alright." She reads the current room's question.

It is uncompleted.

> 7/4 = ?
She tries to remember if anything of significance has happened on the date 7/4.
No, not really.
She types 0.6.
The input clears itself and hologram Sheeval materializes again. “No.” He disappears.
"It's a seventh of four. This query is nonsense." She leaves to check the puzzle room Zita already solved.
❤️🧡💛 \_ \_ is displayed as the prompt. On what looks like a tablet, the answer has been drawn, that being 💚💙.
Okay. She checks the room Zita is in.
Zita’s just about done here. The Sheeval Hologram finishes speaking and she turns around when you enter. “Ah, hello.”
"Hello." She reads the question.

This one is divided into three paragraphs and has three different locations for input, all of which Zita has answered. It describes a situation where an out of control Earth streetcar is going to run over and kill multiple people, but a lever may be activated to kill only one person instead. The second describes the same scenario but the outcome is achieved by pushing a man onto the tracks. The third replaces the one person with “your spouse or child”.

This seems way more personal and morbid than everything else???
Joliene tilts her head, but does not have much more of a response to give. "The prompt you left me with stumped me. Has anything of significance happened on the date 7/4?"

“Ah, um… no, not to my knowledge. I think it’s referring to… a mathematics thing.” She looks down. “I wasn’t taught that kind of subject matter, and I’ve never found it relevant to study on my own, so, er…”
"I see. Well, no matter. Our cognitive abilities have been tried thoroughly. We should check to see if the door has been left unlocked."

Zita stares at Joliene. “Oh.”

She opens the final door. Which is unlocked.
"Wonderful." She walks through.

There’s a lot of different long passages connecting to each other in this underground complex, but there’s one direction that very obviously has commotion coming from it.

“Do you know where we’re going?” Zita looks around confused.
"I should." She continues ushering Zita down the obvious direction.

Blah blah blah skipping filler walking. They come to a door with a shouting match happening just through it.

Zita slowly breathes in and out. “Okay. Whatever comes… I’m ready. Let’s get out of here.”
